Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the #oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, crack the @egg{1} into a #medium bowl{} and whisk.

Put the @breadcrumbs{50%g} and @dried rosemary{1%sachet} into another #bowl{}, season with the @salt{} for the breadcrumbs and @pepper{}.

Cut each @British chicken thighs{2} into 2-3 pieces (depending on size), then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Dip the chicken into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely coated. Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging and discard any excess egg.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{} to coat the bottom of the pan.

> You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan and fry until golden-brown, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Once golden, pop the chicken onto another baking tray and bake on the middle shelf until cooked through, ~{8-11%minutes}.

> The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @dried cranberries{30%g}.

Slice the @French Camembert{125%g} into even pieces.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @wholegrain mustard{17%g} and @mayonnaise{64%g}.

In a medium bowl, combine the @coleslaw mix{120%g}, cranberries and half the mustard mayo (you'll use the rest later). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside.

Halve the @burger buns{2}(sliced).

When the chicken is ready, remove the tray from the #oven and lay the Camembert slices on top of the chicken.

Add the burger buns to the tray and pop back into the #oven until the cheese has melted and the buns have warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, transfer the burger buns to your plates.

Spread the @onion marmalade{30%g} over the bun bases, then top with the cheesy chicken, making sure to spoon on any remaining melted Camembert from the tray.

Spread the remaining mustard mayo onto the bun lids, then sandwich together.

Serve your craft burgers with the chips and cranberry mustard slaw alongside.

Enjoy!